        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLooks like there's been some regression here since now the SDNC healthcheck seems to be failing again to the same issue I mentioned previously (and was already successfully fixed once?) i.e.\n\n nexus3.onap.org:10001/onap/sdnc-image:2.1-STAGING-latest defines feature dependency         <bundle>mvn:org.onap.ccsdk.sli.core/sliPluginUtils-provider/1.1.0-SNAPSHOT</bundle> in /opt/opendaylight/system/org/onap/sdnc/northbound/sdnc-vnftools/2.1.0-SNAPSHOT/sdnc-vnftools-2.1.0-SNAPSHOT-features.xml, but the image actually only has /opt/opendaylight/system/org/onap/ccsdk/sli/core/ccsdk-sliPluginUtils/1.0.2\n\n\nIs there any chance that this contributed to the problem somehow? https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ci-management/+/116262 (combined with earlier https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ccsdk/distribution/+/116082)\n\nI already found that the rewritten versioning in the above changes had wider effect that I expected (I'm trying to remedy that now in https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ccsdk/distribution/+/116381), and those jobs were merged just before SDNC healthcheck started failing.",
